===Verb===
{{en-infl-reg-consonant|open||}}

# {{transitive}}: The action of making something accessible or removing an obstacle to something being accessible (e.g. opening a door to access the room behind it).
# {{transitive}}: To bring up (a topic). (''I don't want to open that subject.'')
# {{transitive}}: To prepare (an establishment) to conduct business.  (''I will open the shop an hour early tomorrow.'')
# {{transitive}}: To start (a campaign.)
# {{intransitive}}: To become open.  (''The door opened.'')
# {{intransitive}}:  To begin conducting business. (''The shop opens at 9:00.'')
# {{intransitive}}, {{cricket}}: To [[begin]] a [[side]]'s [[innings]] as one of the first two [[batsmen]].

